f there was too much money in the political space.<\/p>\n<p>&ldquo;I don&rsquo;t remember seeing big newspaper articles about George Soros or Tom Steyer. The media doesn&rsquo;t like one of money but it&rsquo;s OK with another kind of money,&rdquo; she said to applause. &ldquo;Everyone has a right to speech in this country. And as we all know, any kind of speech costs money.&rdquo;<\/p>\n<p>Fiorina, who unsuccessfully ran for Senate in California in 2010, is running on her outsider credentials. She badly trails her rivals and is at risk of missing the cutoff threshold for Thursday&rsquo;s primetime debate in Cleveland. She insists it&rsquo;s too soon to tell if she will get a podium or not. &ldquo;We don&rsquo;t know what debate we&rsquo;re in yet and we don&rsquo;t know which polls (organizers are using to draw the cutoff,)&rdquo; Fiorina said. &ldquo;I have the lowest name ID of anyone running. Over half the nation has never heard my name.&rdquo;<\/p>\n<p>Compare that with former Florida Gov. Jeb Bush, whom she jabbed as a member of the political dynasty that could see its third member elected President. &ldquo;We have festering problems in Washington, D.C.: a government that has grown bigger, more powerful, more intrusive, more costly, more inept, more corrupt for 40 plus years,&rdquo; Fiorina said. &ldquo;Why do you think you are the Bush who can change that?&rdquo;<\/p>\n","read_more":true,"section":{"name":"Politics","slug":"politics","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/politics\/","description":"Political insight from the Beltway and beyond. Covering the White House, elections, primaries, Congress, domestic policy, foreign policy, the military and more","politics":true},"tag":{"name":"Carly Fiorina","slug":"carly-fiorina","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/tag\/carly-fiorina\/"},"tags":"2016 Election|Carly Fiorina|jeb bush","hero":{"class":"landscape","thumbnail":"http:\/\/i0.wp.com\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2015\/08\/carly-fiorina.jpg?crop=86px%2C60px%2C271px%2C271px&re